    estimated in Karnataka stood at 406, against estimate of 308 Tigers in Madhya Pradesh.",

    'ptiger_learning' => "Learning lessons from the results of All India Tiger Census 2014, a focused approach toward conservation and management was taken up by the Forest Department and the census of 2018 was taken as a mission. In Madhya Pradesh the frontline staff regularly reported of Tigers
